  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The bug report describes missing PCI subdevice entries for Intel Wireless-AC 9260 (device ID 0x2526) with subdevice IDs 0x4010, 0x4018, and 0x401C. These entries are not present in the iwl_dev_info_table static data structure (defined at line 978 in drv.c). Without these entries, the PCI probe function cannot find device-specific configurations for these subdevice variants and falls back to the generic PCI_ANY_ID match, which uses an inappropriate firmware configuration. This causes firmware loading to fail for these specific device combinations. The missing entries should follow the pattern of the existing 0x4030 entry (line 995), which uses iwl9560_2ac_160_cfg configuration for similar 0x40xx subdevice IDs."
}

